class WeatherSimulator {
  private int temperature;
  private boolean isRaining;

  public WeatherSimulator(int temperature, boolean isRaining) {
    this.temperature = temperature;
    this.isRaining = isRaining;
  }

  public void adjustTemperature(int change) {
    this.temperature += change;
  }

  public void triggerRain(boolean startRain) {
    this.isRaining = startRain;
  }

  public boolean isSuitableForHiking() {
    return this.temperature > 20 && !this.isRaining;
  }
}
",

If you find that it recently became unsuitable for hiking, can you definitively conclude that it started raining?
